properties.description: Posted by Annaleen 17 West 32nd St., New York, NYMy favorite reasonably-priced hotel in Manhattan. Located in Midtown, it\'s an easy walk to the Village or Uptown. Plus, it\'s in Koreatown, so there are lots of yummy restaurants nearby. The best part? La Quinta has FREE WiFi. Oh yes.

properties.name: The Living Room Coffee Bar
properties.description: Posted by Annaleen  733 Broadway Avenue, Saskatoon, SaskatchewanMy favorite place to drink coffee and hang out in Saskatoon. The capuccino is great. There are big overstuffed chairs, delicious scones, even more delicious plates of baked brie, and lots of cute people to look at. If you sit near the window, you can get free wifi. Even when it\'s 30 below outside, the Living Room is toasty warm!
